4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING HEALTH INSURANCE LAW TO REQUIRE COVERAGE
5 OF CERTAIN INJECTABLE MEDICINES TO IMPROVE GLUCOSE OR WEIGHT LOSS; PROVIDING
6 REQUIREMENTS FOR COVERAGE; PROVIDING EXCEPTIONS; AND AMENDING SECTIONS 2-18-704, 33-
7 31-111, AND 33-35-306, MCA.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Coverage for injectable medicines to improve glucose or weight
12 loss. (1) Each individual policy, certificate of insurance, or membership contract that is delivered, issued for
13 delivery, renewed, extended, or modified in this state must provide coverage for all types of medically
14 necessary, as determined by a physician licensed to practice medicine in all of its branches, injectable
15 medicines prescribed on-label or off-label to improve glucose or weight loss for use by adults diagnosed or
16 previously diagnosed with prediabetes, gestational diabetes, or obesity.
17 (2) To continue to qualify for coverage under this section, the continued treatment must be
18 medically necessary, and covered members shall, if given advance, written notice, participate in a lifestyle
19 management plan administered by their health plan.
20 (3) This section does not apply to individuals covered by a medicare advantage prescription drug
21 plan.
